<p><span class="style16">Or, you can request a painting for zero dollars. That&#8217;s cool with me too!</span></p>
<p><strong>Some notes about my terrible business model:</strong></p>
<p>It seems many people think I&#8217;m making a bunch of money on this project. Let me assure you that is not the case. My donation money goes back into the project. This &#8220;pay what you want&#8221; style has become popular recently but it only works with digital goods like music and software that can easily and instantly be replicated over and over with no cost for each individual copy. I have to create each one of these paintings by hand, one a day, so to be giving most of these away at no charge is terribly impractical. Yet I continue on with my quixotic endeavor because it&#8217;s fun and you should have some of my art!</p>
<p><strong>Another reason why this is splendid:</strong></p>
<p>The more people that request paintings, the better I get at painting and the more famous I get, the more my paintings are worth. Everybody wins!</p>
<p>So <a href="mailto:freepaintings@alispagnola.com">email me</a>. I want to make you something.</p>

				
